# scripts/.sync-exclude — paths to skip when running scripts/sync-from-main.sh
#
# One bash glob per line. If EVERY file touched by an upstream commit
# matches at least one of these globs, the commit is auto-skipped during
# `./scripts/sync-from-main.sh`. Lines starting with `#` and blank lines
# are ignored.
#
# Globs use bash `[[ "$file" == $pat ]]` semantics:
#   src/app/foo/*           — direct children of src/app/foo (one level)
#   src/app/foo/**          — anything under src/app/foo (any depth)
#   *.md                    — any markdown file at any depth (NOT what bash
#                             does by default — use **/*.md instead)
#   **/*.md                 — markdown files anywhere
#
# These are the directories the lite repo has historically opted out of.
# Uncomment to activate. Leave commented (the default) to track main 1:1.
#
# src/app/assistant/**
# src/components/assistant/**
# src/components/embedded-terminal.tsx
# src/components/terminal-drawer.tsx
#
# Touch this file from the project root to make changes visible to git
# (it's tracked); ./scripts/.sync-state is gitignored.
